      "writtenOn": "2026-03-06T10:55:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think crash is the wrong term. It\u0027s a validation. There are lots of situations where you might inadvertently have an inconsistent workspace, and don\u0027t want the generated manifest to to also inherit that inconsistency.\n\nFor example:\n1. `repo init`\n2. `repo sync` - Fails halfway through and you don\u0027t check the error, some directories are left without a worktree (though arguably you should always notice that error here)\n3. `repo manifest -r` - Now only returns half of the manifest, without warning you about it.\n\nOther examples: You accidentally remove a directory, permission error, the build system removes a directory. In automation this could lead to very difficult to diagnose errors further down the line. The key to reliable automation is to check and fail early.",
      "parentUuid": "5e76b4e5_92b36216",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 18,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 17
