      "writtenOn": "2026-03-13T07:39:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hence why i suggested to improve the error message from a stacktrace to something more descriptive 😊\n\n------------------------------\n\nPretty error or not, `repo` typically always operates with the **manifest as the source of truth**. Changing that is in my view unexpected and opens up risk for accidents. To operate with a partial manifest, there is `repo init -g` where repos can be included or excluded.\n\nI agree that the `repo manifest -r` is a bit of a hybrid, allowing some leeway there is valid. It\u0027s still only called `--revision-as-HEAD` though, so i still expect the *structure* of the manifest to be respected. If not, it opens up many ambiguities\n* Was the repo intentionally missing from the workspace or by mistake?\n* Should it exclude the project or fall back to the revision from the original manifest instead? \n* Should it even include *new* `.git` directories that were not part of the manifest before.\n\nYou could see it as a spectrum:\n\n* `repo manifest` - Manifest as 100 % source of truth\n* `repo manifest -r` - Manifest as source of truth with strictly ONLY revisions replaced. Same behaviour as it has today.\n* `repo manifest -r --permissive` - Intersection of manifest and whatever repos that happen to be present in the workspace. \n   Maybe give it a completely new exclusive flag instead of overloading the `-r` behavior?\n* `repo generate` (imaginary new command) - Generate a manifest based only on found `.git` directories. Without consulting any original manifest \n\nNote that I don\u0027t deny the usefulness of this command, I\u0027m just questioning the default of silently ignoring missing repos. As bare minimum i think the behaviour should be documented and a warning should be printed when repos are missing, but even that is a bit shaky as it would be difficult to detect in automation. When it comes to something as sensitive as manifest, i believe to lean on the side of caution over saving a few keystrokes, for something that at least to me looks like a quite rare operation. \n\n-------\n\nTo be clear, I\u0027m not a `repo` maintainer so my review might not carry a lot of weight here, would be good to hear their perspective.",
      "parentUuid": "8cecba1f_a5caf944",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 18,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 17
      },
