      "side": 1,
      "message": "There\u0027s no backwards compatibility concern in fixing an unhandled exception — nobody\u0027s automation depends on getting a Python stacktrace (hopefully).\n\nI don\u0027t also at all the idea of going around adding flags that needs to be added in any invocation to get correct behavior.That\u0027s how CLIs become unnecessary complex both in use an in maintenance.\n\nIMHO if someone really likes the previous behavior (i.e. they want to get the stacktrace) they can always stay on whatever version they have now. Not being snarky here, just practical.",
